      <div class="container-fluid text-center text-light">
         <h1>About Us</h1>
         <p>The Roman Catholic Diocese of Bridgetown (Latin: Dioecesis Pontipolitana) is a diocese of the Latin Rite of
            the Roman Catholic Church in the Caribbean. The diocese encompasses the entirety of the former British
            dependency of Barbados. The diocese is a suffragan of the Archdiocese of Port of Spain, and a member of the
            Antilles Episcopal Conference.

            Erected in 1970 as the Diocese of Bridgetown-Kingstown, the diocese was split on 23 October 1989 into the
            Diocese of Bridgetown and the Diocese of Kingstown. In September 2011, Father Jason Gordon was consecrated
            Bishop of this Diocese, after the retirement of Bishop Malcolm Galt in May 2005. Both Bishops Malcolm Galt
            and Jason Gordon are clergy native to Trinidad .</p>
